for exec and icon just go to the installation directory of your app 
make a .desktop file in cd /usr/share/applications with the name of your app or whatever
then paste this config and change accordingly
for apps installed from snap use cd /var/lib/snapd/desktop/applications

command to make a user into sudoer   sudo gpasswd -a “username” sudo

[Desktop Entry]
Name=Mathlab
Type=Application
Exec=change
Icon=change
Terminal=false (some programs need this such as matlab)



extra options
[Desktop Entry]
Comment=Mathlab useless
Keywords=Mathlab;mathlab;m; helps in search maybe
StartupNotify=true
